STEP 1 — Create n8n Webhook
In n8n:
Add Node:
✅ Webhook
Settings:

HTTP Method: POST
Path: argo-may-validate
Example URL n8n gives:

https://n8n.yourdomain/webhook/argo-may-validate
👉 Copy this URL.
STEP 2 — Add PostSync Hook in Argo CD
Inside your MAY application manifest.
Add a Kubernetes Job as PostSync hook.
Example YAML
YAML
apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
  name: notify-n8n
  annotations:
    argocd.argoproj.io/hook: PostSync
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: curl
        image: curlimages/curl
        command:
        - curl
        - -X
        - POST
        - https://n8n.yourdomain/webhook/argo-may-validate
      restartPolicy: Never
✅ What Happens Now
Whenever Argo CD finishes syncing:

PostSync Hook Runs
        ↓
Calls n8n automatically
        ↓
Workflow starts
ZERO manual action.
